38 class CompareFunc
39 {
40 public:
41  typedef double ARGS;
42 
44  static std::string typeName() { return "CompareFunc"; }
45 
46  CompareFunc(double tol) : m_tolerance(tol) {}
47 
48  virtual ~CompareFunc() {}
49 
50  bool compare(Mutation::Mixture& mix, Eigen::VectorXd result)
51  {
52  Eigen::VectorXd v(result.size());
53  compute(mix, v);
54  bool matches = v.isApprox(result, m_tolerance);
55 
56  if (!matches) {
57  std::cout << "Comparison between {"
58  << v.transpose() << "} and {"
59  << result.transpose() << "} failed."
60  << std::endl;
61  }
62 
63  return matches;
64  };
65 
66  virtual void compute(Mutation::Mixture& mix, Eigen::VectorXd& v) = 0;
67 
68 private:
69  double m_tolerance;
70 };

72 // Macro for adding a new comparison function
73 #define ADD_FUNCTION(__NAME__,__CODE__)\
74 class __NAME__ : public CompareFunc\
75 {\
76 public:\
77  __NAME__(double tol) : CompareFunc(tol) {}\
78 protected:\
79  void compute(Mutation::Mixture& mix, Eigen::VectorXd& v) {\
80  __CODE__;\
81  };\
82 };\
83 Mutation::Utilities::Config::ObjectProvider<\
84  __NAME__, CompareFunc> op_##__NAME__(#__NAME__);
85 
86 // Available comparison functions
87 ADD_FUNCTION(electron_thermal_conductivity_3, v(0) = mix.electronThermalConductivity(3))
88 ADD_FUNCTION(electron_thermal_conductivity_2, v(0) = mix.electronThermalConductivity(2))
89 ADD_FUNCTION(heavy_thermal_conductivity, v(0) = mix.heavyThermalConductivity())
90 ADD_FUNCTION(internal_thermal_conductivity, v(0) = mix.internalThermalConductivity(mix.T()))
91 ADD_FUNCTION(sigma_1st_order, v(0) = mix.electricConductivity(1))
92 ADD_FUNCTION(sigma_2nd_order, v(0) = mix.electricConductivity(2))
93 ADD_FUNCTION(heavy_thermal_diffusion_ratios, mix.heavyThermalDiffusionRatios(v.data()))
94 ADD_FUNCTION(viscosity, v(0) = mix.viscosity())
